He attended secondary school at Mfantsipim School in Cape Coast, Ghana, and at the Presbyterian Boys’ Senior High School in Accra, Ghana. While at Mfantsipim, have invented a corn-planting machine dat won the national science competition and graduated as the valedictorian of the Class of 1981. He RECEIVED his BS and MS in electrical engineering in 1989 from Johns Hopkins University and his PhD in computation and neural systems in 1997 from the California Institute of Technology , where he was advised by Carver Mead . For his PhD thesis, Boahen designed and fabricated a silicon chip emulating the functioneren of the retina. [2] Boahen’s Father, Albert Adu Boahen , was a professor of history at the University of Ghana and an advocate for democracy in Ghana.

snippet.textDisplay:
Why do we need Jesus?

We are in a fallen world full of wickedness, pain, and suffering,  separated from God by sin. So what must be done to restore fellowship with God? First we must be genuine about our own sins. Look at the 10 commandments and see how you stack up, it is a mirror showing us our sinful nature. We have all broken the moral law and deserve his wrath and judgement.

The Gospel:

At the same time the Father is so rich in mercy and loves us so much that he sent his Son in the flesh 2000 years ago, who lived a sinless life on our behalf, was gruesomely tortured and mocked by his own creation, died a horrific death on the cross in place of US filthy sinners, and rose from the dead 3 days later proving he is the Great I Am. He paid the fine for our death sentence on the cross thus satisfying God's justice, setting us free from sin and the Law. Once we realize our sinful nature,  we must repent for our sins, and put our full trust in the Lord and Savior Jesus Christ like you'd put faith in a parachute. Do this and you will be born again. He will instantly grant you the Holy Spirit which will live in you, eternal life in a united heaven and earth, a new heart that loves righteousness, and relationship with God will be made right, not by our good works or observance of the law, but by his AMAZING GRACE and mercy. That's His promise. Think about this, it's the greatest gift you could ever receive, and it's from the very Being that created you :). Humbly ask him to reveal himself to you. If you have a Bible I invite you to read the book of John. Jesus loves you, I love you, peace.
